"Zhang D.-Q., Zhang L., Yang J., Feng G.-L.","The impact of temperature and precipitation variation on drought in China in last 50 years",2010,"Wuli Xuebao/Acta Physica Sinica","59","1",,"655","663",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-75849151532&partnerID=40&md5=5cbf2f296fa487b4ae5658ff0fb367c9","College of Atmospheric Sciences, Lanzhou University, Lanzhou 730000, China; Key Laboratory of Regional Climate-Environment for Temperate East Asia, Institute of Atmospheric Physics, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100029, China; Laboratory for Climate Studies of China Meteorological Administration, National Climate Center, Beijing 100081, China","Zhang, D.-Q., College of Atmospheric Sciences, Lanzhou University, Lanzhou 730000, China, Key Laboratory of Regional Climate-Environment for Temperate East Asia, Institute of Atmospheric Physics, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100029, China; Zhang, L., College of Atmospheric Sciences, Lanzhou University, Lanzhou 730000, China; Yang, J., Laboratory for Climate Studies of China Meteorological Administration, National Climate Center, Beijing 100081, China; Feng, G.-L., Key Laboratory of Regional Climate-Environment for Temperate East Asia, Institute of Atmospheric Physics, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100029, China, Laboratory for Climate Studies of China Meteorological Administration, National Climate Center, Beijing 100081, China","Based on homogeneous temeperature, precipitation and the Palmer Drought Severity Index (PDSI) data between 1958 and 2007 of 194 stations in China, quantitative measure of impact of global warming and precipitation variation on the formation of drought in China is made through a statistical model. Dividing China into eight regions, we analyzed the importance of global warming and precipitation variations in each region respectively. Under the background of global warming, the trend of drought in north China still persists. The most probable region of drought in the next five years shows a tendendy of expansion in north China, especially in the direction to the south. Decreased precipitation is still the key factor in drought formation in most regions. However, in the north, northeast and east-northwest China, global warming plays a bigger role in drought formation. © Chin.Phys.Soc.","Drought; Global warming; Precipitation",,,,,,,"Soloman, S., Qin, D.H., Manning, M., Alley, R.B., Berntsen, T., (2007) Climate Change 2007: The Physical Science Basis. Working Group I Contribution to the IPCC Fourth Assessment Report, p. 61. , (Cambridge: Cambridge University Press); Dai, A.G., Trenberth, K.E., Qian, T.T., (2004) J. Hydrometeor., 5, p. 1117; Ma, Z.G., Fu, C.B., (2006) Chin. Sci. Bull., 51, p. 2429. , (in Chinese); Ma, Z.G., Ren, X.B., (2005) Adv. Clim. Chan. Res., 3, p. 195. , (in Chinese); Zhang, Q.Y., Chen, L.T., (1991) Chin. J. Atmos. Sci., 15, p. 72. , (in Chinese); Richard, G.Z., (1994) Climate Biosphere Interaction: Biogenic Emissions and Environmental Effects of Climate Change, p. 77. , (New York: John Wiley & Sons); Ma, Z.G., Fu, C.B., (2001) Acta Meteorol. Sin., 59, p. 737. , (in Chinese); Ma, Z.G., (2005) Chin. J. Geophy., 48, p. 1011. , (in Chinese); Dai, A.G., Trenberth, K.E., Karl, T.R., (1998) Geophys. Res. Lett., 25, p. 3367; Karl, T.R., (1983) J. Clim. Appl. Meteorol., 22, p. 1356; Karl, T.R., (1986) J. Clim. Appl. Meteorol., 25, p. 77; Karl, T.R., Koscielny, A.J., (1982) J. Clim., 2, p. 313; Nkemdirim, L., Weber, L., (1999) J. Clim., 12, p. 2434; Liang, X.J., (1997) Normaility Testing, p. 126. , (Beijing: China Statistics Press) (in Chinese); Shapiro, S.S., Wilk, M.B., (1965) Biometrika, 52, p. 591; Ding, Y.G., (1994) Sci. Atmos. Sin., 18, p. 552. , (in Chinese); Cao, J., Tao, Y., (2002) J. Nat. Disast., 11, p. 115. , (in Chinese); Hu, W.D., Chen, X.G., Li, Y.C., Zheng, G.F., Shao, J., Zhang, Z., Na, L., (2006) J. Des. Res., 6, p. 1036. , (in Chinese); Wang, Y., Shi, N., Gu, J.Q., Feng, G.L., Zhang, L.B., (2006) Chin